hould be your focal point.";i:19;s:49:"Your front door should make a fun bold statement.";i:20;s:52:"Read 6 Most Popular Colors to Paint Your Front Door.";i:21;s:134:"Your garage door does NOT need to match the front door especially if you have a door that is a powerful color like red yellow or blue.";i:22;s:48:"In that case it should not match the front door.";i:23;s:27:"Garage Door Paint Overview.";i:24;s:87:"Our Garage Door Paint is a solvent-based coating designed for use on both metal timber.";i:25;s:98:"Based on a urethane modified resin system which provides a strong durable UV resistant paint film.";i:26;s:130:"Selection of high quality pigments further enhances the properties by providing improved weathering resistance and light fastness.";i:27;s:60:"Garage door springs are color coded for easy identification.";i:28;s:72:"See our easy to use selection guide for help choosing the right springs.";i:29;s:65:"Dark blue note that some other companies use blue for both 90 lb.";i:30;s:54:"If your springs are blue double-check the door weight.";i:31;s:52:"How To Paint A Garage Door - Ace Hardware - YouTube.";i:32;s:103:"Years ago with my first house in Houston TX I painted garage door a darker blue and lived to regret it.";i:33;s:92:"In hindsite I should have painted the garage door the house color instead of the trim color.";i:34;s:22:"The color faded badly.";i:35;s:81:"And I was so excited about the windows in the door but that too did not work out.";i:36;s:139:"This Oxford blue high sheen garage door paint has been specially designed to give a durable and long-lasting finish on a range of surfaces.";i:37;s:124:"Simply apply with a brush or roller and leave for 4-6 hours to dry - a great way to give the surfaces additional protection.";i:38;s:33:"Covers 7m² per litre on average.";i:39;s:26:"Suitable for Garage doors.";i:40;s:76:"A coat of blue paint on the front door can quickly refresh a dated exterior.";i:41;s:127:"This classic brick facade with traditional detailing gets a modern update with a splashy cerulean blue paint color on the door.";i:42;s:66:"Set off by the red brick the bold shade offers a high-energy look.";i:43;s:43:"Modern Masters Royal Blue Front Door Paint.";i:44;s:140:"Modern Masters is a durable high quality paint that comes in a variety of really nice colors including this shade of royal blue called Calm.";i:45;s:65:"Suitable for exterior metal fiberglass or wood doors or shutters.";i:46;s:50:"Water-based formula provides long last durability.";i:47;s:105:"How to Clean Your Painted Garage Door To keep a garage door looking fresh you need to clean it regularly.";i:48;s:25:"Ideally every six months.";i:49;s:98:"First clean off with a brush and wash down with a garden hose to get rid of loose dirt and debris.";i:50;s:105:"Next get a bucket of warm water with a squeeze of washing up liquid and wash down the door with a sponge.";i:51;s:102:"Homes with red-painted or vinyl siding commonly have dark brown beige or even light-grey garage doors.";i:52;s:65:"To add more colors try a blue garage door maybe a more navy blue.";i:53;s:80:"Find the shade and tone the pairs well with the exact shade of red on your home.";i:54;s:86:"Be careful if painting your garage door white if you have red-painted or vinyl siding.";i:55;s:173:"There are many blue shades that can be used for a garage door you can have a deep blue door a stormy hue turquoise aqua marine blue midnight blue there is no end of choices.";i:56;s:157:"Blue can also be very classic and timeless but make sure that whatever type of blue color youve chosen it has to blend or complement your homes overall look.";i:57;s:81:"If your garage door isnt great looking a coat of paint will only help to hide it.";i:58;s:208:"Hiding your garage door will draw attention to other parts of the house and if youve done recent exterior work its a good bet to put your garage door in the background with a color that blends into the house.";i:59;s:33:"So what color should a garage be.";i:60;s:186:"I recommend white but if you want something a bit different then paint your garage a light shade of gray beige or blue because lighter shades make a room seem bigger than it actually is.";i:61;s:109:"The color of your walls also needs to compliment your cabinets and floor so the entire garage looks cohesive.";i:62;s:56:"Youll also want to take a look around your neighborhood.";i:63;s:136:"If most of your neighbors have brown garage doors your house might draw unwanted attention if you paint your garage door turquoise blue.";i:64;s:71:"The goal isnt to blend in with your neighbors but to encourage harmony.";i:65;s:45:"Best Front Door Paint Colors for Blue Houses.";i:66;s:66:"You can use just about any color for front doors with blue houses.";i:67;s:84:"We love red orange green white black blue gray and warm wood stains for blue houses.";i:68;s:76:"We note each of them in the photos below but these are two of our favorites.";}}